headline: Rocco Commisso, Who Built Cable Empire From ‘Scraps’ That Others Shunned, Dies at 76
summary: When the cable industry was consolidating around the nation’s largest cities, he went small to create one of the biggest cable companies in the U.S.

headline: How Streaming Became Cable TV’s Unlikely Life Raft
summary: Charter Communications and other providers are slowing the cord-cutting exodus by bundling the very apps that once threatened their survival.
